Task 3 – Notes

In this task, I explored both coding practice platforms and collaboration tools. For the coding part, I created an account on a platform like HackerRank/CodeChef and completed a beginner-level problem. This helped me understand how coding platforms work and how they can be used to improve problem-solving skills step by step. It was interesting to see how even simple problems require logical thinking and accuracy.

For the collaboration part, I used Google Forms to create a Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz with five questions. I included different types of questions such as multiple choice and short answer. I also viewed the responses in Google Sheets, which showed how data can be collected and analysed easily.

Initially, I found it slightly challenging to design meaningful quiz questions and understand the interface of the platforms. However, after exploring, it became easier and more intuitive. These tools will be very useful in my academic journey, as coding platforms will help me practise regularly, while Google Workspace tools will help in collaboration, surveys, and project work.
